Written evidence submitted by David Mackenzie[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]I wholly support the stance and recommendations of the briefing paper “Towards a comprehensive land reform agenda for Scotland” (
[normal]James Hunter, Peter Peacock, Andy Wightman and Michael 
[normal]Foxley
[normal]).
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]In particular I support:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]I am writing as an ordinary citizen we believes that the land is not only our key asset but o
[normal]ur major responsibility for the present and the future.
[normal] 
[normal]The control of this asset and the discharge of the responsibility are severely distorted by the current pattern of formal ownership. This has to change.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]October 2013
